The paper deals with knowledge base completion and relation prediction in knowledge graphs using neural network models. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and attention mechanisms for feature embedding and prediction also suggests relevance to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also deals with the representation and manipulation of large amounts of structured data, which is a key aspect of database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of embeddings and similarity measures for information retrieval is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
